<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Good question. I went back and read in Chapter 113. Alex punches Kyle so hard as to render him unconscious. Then:<br/><br/>“ I stepped away from the body crumpl<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Good question. I went back and read in Chapter 113. Alex punches Kyle so hard as to render him unconscious. Then:<br /><br />“ I stepped away from the body crumpled on the floor. The spike of the ice pick was still embedded in my chest. It had to come out. I knew I couldn’t, shouldn’t, do it myself. I needed to get to a hospital. Maybe Dr. Kate McTiernan would take care of me. <br />‘“I made a phone call. A very important call. <br />“This was just the beginning, wasn’t it? Sure it was.”<br /><br />I suspect that whomever he called was not an answering machine but a real person surrounded by Sampson and the FBI agents, who put the call on speakerphone. Probably plenty of cell phones recorded the confession.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
