  <span id="freeText16451099065734365532" style="display:none">In this edition, Alex cross is on the case of lunatics who beleiev they are vampires and do drink human blood, all the while dealing with the taunting of a psychopath who calls himself mastermind.<br />I do usually like the Alex cross books i read, they keep you guessing whats coming next. But this particular instalment felt a bit dragged on for me.<br />It felt,as though most of the book was centered more on alex,and,his family rather than solving the case. Yes he was working the case and it was shown but it felt the book wasnst centered on the murders.<br />I'd say 2.5 rounded up to a 3.</span>
